      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BRAILEY BANNER (2) was out of character last run when missing the frame, finishing seventh (24.25) in a Grade 5 at Richmond. Generally safe to begin but was always well back last time. Should be very hard to beat this time. LEVI DESIGN (5) is a progressive type who recorded his 8th career win last time out (17.79) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including six wins. The form out of his last race has been franked. Deserves serious consideration again. DESPICABLE RAMBO (3) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Kept coming to fill the minor placings over 400m at Maitland (22.82) in a Grade 5. Strike rate this course and distance strong having won eight of 16 tries. Expected to be in the finish again. CHARING CROSS (1) has strong credentials at this circuit over this journey.",
